cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CV

The paper discusses sketching techniques for scaling up machine learning algorithms, which is a topic closely related to the field of machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses optimization techniques such as preconditioning and conjugate gradient, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of sketching techniques for reducing the dimensionality of data sets suggests that it may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of sketching techniques in computer vision, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Finally, the paper discusses the use of random projection, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory).
